-- European Stocks Decline as Banks, Miners Retreat; U.S. Index Futures Drop
-- B y   D a v i d   M e r r i t t
-- 2010-09-23T08:36:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-23/european-stocks-decline-as-banks-miners-retreat-u-s-index-futures-drop.html
European stocks declined for a
third day, led by basic-resources companies and banks. U.S.
index futures slipped, while Asian shares were little changed.  The benchmark Stoxx Europe 600 Index fell 0.5 percent to
259.98 at 9:33 a.m. in London, extending yesterday’s 1.4 percent
slump. Credit Suisse Group AG led bank stocks lower, falling 2.8
percent, while BHP Billiton Ltd., the world’s largest mining
company, fell 1.5 percent.  Futures on the Standard & Poor’s 500 Index lost 0.3
percent, while the MSCI Asia Pacific Index slid less than 0.1
percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
